    {
      "collapsed": true,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 21 },
      "id": 9,
      "title": "Tail Sampling diagnostics (Phase 11)",
      "type": "row",
      "description": "POLICY-NAMES CONTRACT (Phase 11 D-T16): the policy= labels referenced in this row's queries are a contract with infra/observability/otelcol-config.yaml's tail_sampling.policies block. Renaming any policy in the YAML requires updating these queries. Verified at runtime by `mise run verify:tail-sampling` (D-T14). Also depends on the alpha feature gate `processor.tailsamplingprocessor.recordpolicy` enabled on the otel-collector container (Route A) — without the gate, sub-policy attribution collapses to the outer 'composite-policy' name only.",
      "panels": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 22 },
          "id": 10,
          "title": "Sampling decisions (composite envelope — see Tempo for sub-policy)",
          "type": "timeseries",
          "description": "Per-policy sampling decisions per second, by outer composite policy + decision. Under Route A the composite envelope collapses sub-policy attribution at the metric layer — see the Tempo `tailsampling.composite_policy` span attribute for per-sub-policy view (verified by `mise run verify:tail-sampling` Tier 2).",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
              "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 1, "fillOpacity": 10 }
            }
          },
          "options": {
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
            "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
          },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "sum by (policy, decision) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_count_traces_sampled_total[5m]))",
              "legendFormat": "{{policy}} / {{decision}}",
              "refId": "A"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 22 },
          "id": 11,
          "title": "Per-policy not-sample votes",
          "type": "timeseries",
          "description": "Each policy votes sample/not_sampled/dropped per trace; this panel surfaces the not-sampled and dropped votes. Read alongside the decisions panel to see, e.g., probabilistic-fallback's drop-vote rate roughly 4x its sample-vote rate (20% sampling → 80% not-sampled). RESEARCH §3.3 panel 2 — replaces the non-existent `count_spans_dropped` from CONTEXT.md with the canonical per-policy decision='not_sampled' surface.",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
              "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 1, "fillOpacity": 10 }
            }
          },
          "options": {
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
            "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
          },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "sum by (policy, decision) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_count_traces_sampled_total{decision=~\"not_sampled|dropped\"}[5m]))",
              "legendFormat": "{{policy}} / {{decision}}",
              "refId": "A"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 31 },
          "id": 12,
          "title": "Late-arriving spans (Scenario 1 buffer hits)",
          "type": "timeseries",
          "description": "Late span = a span arriving AFTER its trace's sampling decision was made (Scenario 1 of the v0.151.0 README's three late-span scenarios). Low and stable = `decision_wait: 10s` is right-sized. Climbing = traces have spans straggling beyond the window; consider raising decision_wait or enabling decision_cache.sampled_cache_size. Histogram in SECONDS — _count gives event rate; _bucket+histogram_quantile gives lateness distribution. RESEARCH §3.3 panel 3 — replaces the non-existent `late_span_total` from CONTEXT.md with the canonical `sampling_late_span_age` surface.",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
              "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 1, "fillOpacity": 10 }
            }
          },
          "options": {
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
            "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
          },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_late_span_age_count[5m])",
              "legendFormat": "late spans/s",
              "refId": "A"
            },
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_late_span_age_bucket[5m])))",
              "legendFormat": "p99 lateness (seconds)",
              "refId": "B"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 31 },
          "id": 13,
          "title": "Sampling decision-loop latency (p50/p95/p99)",
          "type": "timeseries",
          "description": "Wall-clock time the Collector spends running the per-trace decision loop for one batch. README quote: 'A latency exceeding 1 second can delay sampling decisions beyond decision_wait, increasing the chance of traces being dropped before sampling.' Workshop p99 should stay well under 10ms. RESEARCH §3.3 panel 4 — uses canonical `sampling_decision_timer_latency` (was incorrectly cited as `decision_latency_bucket` in CONTEXT.md). NOTE: the `_milliseconds` unit suffix may or may not be present per RESEARCH §3.2.1; if panel data is empty, drop the `_milliseconds` infix and reload.",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
              "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 1, "fillOpacity": 10 }
            }
          },
          "options": {
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
            "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
          },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_decision_timer_latency_milliseconds_bucket[5m])))",
              "legendFormat": "p50 (ms)",
              "refId": "A"
            },
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_decision_timer_latency_milliseconds_bucket[5m])))",
              "legendFormat": "p95 (ms)",
              "refId": "B"
            },
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_decision_timer_latency_milliseconds_bucket[5m])))",
              "legendFormat": "p99 (ms)",
              "refId": "C"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 31 },
          "id": 14,
          "title": "Traces dropped before decision (buffer pressure)",
          "type": "timeseries",
          "description": "Rate of traces evicted from the tail_sampling buffer BEFORE decision_wait expired — real data loss from buffer pressure. When this is > 0, the composite policy never got to evaluate those traces. Zero is healthy. Sustained > 0 means num_traces (currently 10000) is too small for the incoming trace rate or decision_wait (currently 10s) is too long. The old metric (sampling_traces_on_memory) included decided traces in GC retention and was misleading — it showed the hashmap size, not pending work.",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "red" },
              "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 2, "fillOpacity": 30 },
              "unit": "ops"
            }
          },
          "options": {
            "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
            "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
          },
          "targets": [
            {
              "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
              "expr": "rate(otelcol_processor_tail_sampling_sampling_trace_dropped_too_early_total[5m])",
              "legendFormat": "dropped too early /s",
              "refId": "A"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 40 },
      "id": 15,
      "title": "Exemplars (Phase 12)",
      "type": "row",
      "description": "Phase 12 — ExemplarFilter.traceBased() on both SdkMeterProviders attaches trace_id/span_id to histogram data points when a span is active at record() time. Grafana requests exemplar data from Mimir when panel query targets include exemplar: true. Click any exemplar dot to navigate to the originating trace in Tempo.",
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 41 },
      "id": 16,
      "title": "HTTP Request Duration (with Exemplars)",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "description": "p50/p95/p99 latency percentiles for the producer service's HTTP server. Exemplar dots appear when load is running and the ExemplarFilter.traceBased() pipeline is active — click any dot to open the originating trace in Tempo. Both producer and consumer OtelSdkConfiguration.buildMeterProvider() calls have .setExemplarFilter(ExemplarFilter.traceBased()) (EXMP-01).",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "linear", "lineWidth": 1, "fillOpacity": 10 },
          "unit": "s"
        }
      },
      "options": {
        "exemplarLabel": "trace_id",
        "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.50, sum by (le) (rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p50",
          "refId": "A",
          "exemplar": true
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95",
          "refId": "B",
          "exemplar": true
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(http_server_request_duration_seconds_bucket[5m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99",
          "refId": "C",
          "exemplar": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 50 },
      "id": 17,
      "title": "Log-Based Metrics (Phase 13)",
      "type": "row",
      "description": "Phase 13 — Loki recording rules derive metrics FROM LOGS using LogQL. The ruler evaluates sum(rate({service_name=~\"order-.+\"} |= \"ERROR\" [2m])) every 1m and remote-writes the result to Mimir as log:order_errors:rate2m. No Java code changes — pure YAML. The panel below overlays this log-derived error rate against the SDK-emitted orders.created counter to demonstrate the equivalence (and divergence) of metrics-from-code vs metrics-from-logs.",
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 9, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 51 },
      "id": 18,
      "title": "Log-Based Error Rate vs SDK Counter",
      "type": "timeseries",
      "description": "The gap between the SDK-emitted creation rate and the log-derived error rate is your success rate. The SDK counter is the source of truth; the log-derived metric is an ops-team approximation that requires no code change.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineInterpolation": "linear",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "auto",
            "spanNulls": false
          },
          "unit": "ops"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "list", "placement": "bottom", "showLegend": true },
        "tooltip": { "mode": "single" }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "expr": "sum by (service_name) (rate(orders_created_total[2m]))",
          "legendFormat": "SDK: orders created ({{service_name}})",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
          "expr": "log:order_errors:rate2m",
          "legendFormat": "Logs: errors ({{service_name}})",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
